  "prompt": "I am 17. Should I start taking multivitamins as a supplement to my diet?",
  "response": "Before starting any supplement, including multivitamins, it's important to consider a few factors:\n\n1. **Diet Quality**: If you're eating a balanced diet that includes a variety of fruits, vegetables, whole grains, lean proteins, and healthy fats, you may be getting the essential vitamins and minerals your body needs from food.\n\n2. **Nutritional Gaps**: If you have specific dietary restrictions (such as vegetarianism or veganism) or health conditions that may lead to deficiencies, it might make sense to consider a multivitamin.\n\n3. **Consult with a Healthcare Provider**: It's always a good idea to talk to a healthcare professional or a registered dietitian before starting any supplement. They can help assess your individual nutritional needs and determine whether a multivitamin is necessary.\n\n4. **Dosage and Composition**: If you do decide to take a multivitamin, look for one that is appropriate for your age and gender, as nutrient needs can vary during adolescence.\n\nRemember that supplements should not replace whole foods, which provide a range of nutrients and benefits beyond vitamins and minerals.",
